{{page-title 'First Steps'}}
<div class='w-full h-full p-5 flex flex-row justify-start items-start'>
	<MdcCard class='w-full max-w-full max-h-full'>
		<:header as |Header|>
			<Header class='flex flex-row justify-between items-center border-b'>
				<:headline as |Headline|>
					<Headline @text='README' />
				</:headline>
				<:subheadline as |SubHeadline|>
					<SubHeadline @text='Installation, integration, etc' />
				</:subheadline>
			</Header>
		</:header>
		<:content as |Content|>
			<Content class='overflow-y-auto'>
				<article class='twyr-prose'>
					<h4 class='prose max-w-none'>Installation</h4>
					<p class='twyr-prose'>
						Installation is pretty standard: Use either
						<code class='prose'>ember install @twyr/ember-mdc-web</code>
						or
						<code class='prose'>npm install @twyr/ember-mdc-web</code>
					</p>

					<h4 class='prose max-w-none'>Integration into Ember Apps</h4>
					<p class='twyr-prose prose-strong:underline'>
						<strong>CAVEAT:</strong>
						At this point, the
						<code>build</code>
						hook for Embroider does not seem to be invoking the
						build configurations file. Once that is resolved,
						integrating EMDC Web configurations within the Ember App
						build process should become automatic. For right now,
						however, the following steps should be manually
						configured:
					</p>
					<ol class='twyr-prose'>
						<li class='twyr-prose'>
							Add a div to "contain" the dropdown content
							elements. Ideally, this div should be either the
							first, or the last, element in the
							<code>application.hbs</code>
							file. However, that is just a recommendation, and
							can be placed anywhere in the template.

							{{! prettier-ignore }}
							<pre class='twyr-prose'>
&lt;div id='mdc-abstract-dropdown--content-container' /&gt;</pre>
						</li>
						<li class='twyr-prose'>
							If the ember/npm install script does not
							automatically add
							<code>ember-cli-sass</code>
							and/or
							<code>ember-google-fonts</code>
							to the application's dev-dependencies, add them:

							{{! prettier-ignore }}
							<pre class='twyr-prose'>
ember install ember-cli-sass ember-google-fonts</pre>
						</li>
						<li class='twyr-prose'>
							Add EMDC Web SCSS configuration to the
							<code
							>&lt;ember_app_name&gt;/app/styles/app.scss</code>
							file (change values as necessary):

							{{! prettier-ignore }}
							<pre class='twyr-prose'>
@use "sass:string";

/*
 * Material Design Components for the Web
 */

@use '@twyr/ember-mdc-web/dist/styles/ember-mdc-web' with (
	$primary-colour: &lt;primary_color_rgb&gt;,
	$secondary-colour: &lt;secondary_color_rgb&gt;,
	$error-colour: &lt;error_color_rgb&gt;,
	$surface-colour: &lt;surface_color_rgb&gt;,
	$background-colour: &lt;background_color_rgb&gt;,

	$body-font-family: string.unquote('&lt;body_font_name&gt;,sans-serif'),
	$header-font-family: string.unquote('&lt;headings_font_name&gt;, sans-serif')
);</pre>
						</li>
						<li class='twyr-prose'>
							Add the Google font import configuration to the
							<code
							>&lt;ember_app_name&gt;/config/environment.js</code>
							file:

							{{! prettier-ignore }}
							<pre class='twyr-prose'>
googleFonts: ['Inter', 'Josefin Sans']</pre>
						</li>
					</ol>
					<p class='prose max-w-none'>
						And with that, the Ember App should be ready to consume
						EMDC Web Addon artifacts.
					</p>
				</article>
			</Content>
		</:content>
	</MdcCard>
</div>